oerpenv - Tool to administrate OpenERP environments
Cristian S. Rocha (c) 2011-2015
cristian.rocha@moldeointeractive.com.ar

This code is distributed under the MIT license.

Requirements:
-------------

None for now.

Installation:
-------------

Should suffice with doing:

 python setup.py install

Then the oerpenv command line is available with the following sub-commands:


erpenv [command] [options]
The OpenERP environment administrator help you to administrate OpenERP environments. You can use the following commands.

        oerpenv resetconf               Reset configuration values. 
        
        oerpenv enable [addons]         Enabel addons on the environment. Create a symbolic link.
        
        oerpenv show [object]           Show addon information.
        
        oerpenv update                  Update sources. 
        
        oerpenv newenv [name]           Create a new python environment
        
        oerpenv dummy [addon]           Create a dummy addon. Useful to create new addon.
        
        oerpenv search [object]         Search addon with this object.
        
        oerpenv list-addons             List all availables addons in sources.
        
        oerpenv add [name] [repository] Add a branch to the sources list
        
        oerpenv init [path]             Init an environment to the path. 
        
        oerpenv client                  Execute the server in test mode for this addon.
        
        oerpenv install [env]           Install all software in the environment
        
        oerpenv test [addon]            Execute the server in test mode for this addon.
        
        oerpenv config                  Create client and server configuration files. 
        
All configurations are stored in the environment.conf file. You can setup it by hand or using the available commands.

Usage:
------

 Testing a module:
 -----------------

To create a simple OpenERP instance execute the following commands in some work directory.

$ oerpenv init openerp_env
$ cd openerp_env
$ oerpenv update
$ oerpenv install
$ oerpenv list-addons

Search for an addon to test, like hr_attendance

$ oerpenv enable hr_attendance
$ oerpenv test hr_attendance

Open other terminal and in the same environment directory execute:

$ oerpenv client

Then the client will open and you can work.

 Testing more than one module:
 ----------------------------

If you need test more than one module you can create a dummy addon in the following way:

$ oerpenv dummy hr_test

In the output you can find the source path. There you can found the __openerp__.py file. Append the modules you want to test in the 'depends' field, in this example will use hr_attendace and hr_contract. If you done all right you can execute the follwing command without errors:

$ oerpenv enable hr_test

Then you can execute the server in mode test again, for the new module.

$ oerpenv test hr_test

 Searching for an object in source code:
 --------------------------------------

To search the source code of a code you can use the command 'search'.

 Display addon information:
 -------------------------

To show addon information, like description, declarated objects and path to the source you can use the command 'show'.

